###**v1.0.1**

**Release Date: 20th February 2016**

Features included in this release:

- Updated stemcell to 3146.9
- Fixed machine agent related issue for multiple PCF installations
- TierName, NodeName and UniqueHostID suffixed with DomainName
-  Support for **OpenTSDB Firehose Nozzle**. Support for all Cloud Foundry deployment metrics.

## Upgrade AppDynamics APM ##

1. In Ops Manager, click **Import a Product** to import new tile binary.
  ![Import Product](images/Ops_Manager1.png)

2. Once imported, click **Upgrade** on the left panel for AppDynamics.
  ![Upgrade](images/Ops_Manager2.png)

3. If you have multiple PCF installations, update the **Application Name** for **Machine Agent Extension** so that the Application name for each Machine Agent Extension is unique across PCF installations. Save these changes.
  ![Application Name for MachineAgent](images/Ops_Manager3.png)

4. You might have to import a new stem cell version 3146.9 from  [http://bosh.io/stemcells](http://bosh.io/stemcells).
![Upgrade Stem Cell](images/Ops_Manager4.png)

5. Once the tile is ready, click **Apply Changes**. This will upgrade your tile to version 1.0.1.
  ![Apply Changes](images/Ops_Manager5.png)

6. Once the tile in successfully installed, check all the Cloud Foundry deployment metrics on this path: **Metric Browser > Application Infrastructure Performance > {Tier Name} > Custom Metrics > CF**
![enter image description here](./images/HierarchyMetricBrowser.png)

**For Ops Metrics 1.6.X and above**

 - Ensure the OpenTSDB instance for **Ops Metrics** is configured to run one instance in the Ops Metrics Tile.
  ![enter image description here](./images/OpenTSDB.png)
 - Get the IP address of the JMX Provider VM (Ops metrics VM) from **Ops Metrics Tile > Status**
  ![enter image description here](./images/JMX_IP.png)
 - In the **Ops Manager Director** tile's config page, set the **Metrics IP Address** with value of JMX Provider VM IP address.
  ![enter image description here](./images/OpsManagerDirector.png)